{% block content %}

<h1 class="Article-title">Container</h1>
<p class="c-Text--lead">Contains page elements to a reasonable maximum width based on the size of a user's screen.</p>

<p>This is useful to couple with other UI elements like <strong>grid</strong> or <strong>menu</strong> to restrict their width to a reasonable size for display.</p>

<hr class="Article-divider">

<h2 id="section:usage"><a href="section:usage" class="c-Text--resetLink">Usage</a></h2>

<p>The maximum width of the Container object is defined in "stylesheets/settings/_settings.global.scss" with the variable <code>$g-site-max-width</code>. It is set to <strong>1200px</strong> by default.</p>

<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
<pre><code class="xml">&lt;div class=&quot;o-Container&quot;&gt;
  ...
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h2 id="section:classes"><a href="section:classes" class="c-Text--resetLink">Classes</a></h2>

<div class="scrollXauto">
  <table class="c-Table c-Table--striped">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th class="o-Size--1of4 c-Text--left">Class</th>
        <th class="c-Text--left">Description</th>
        <th class="c-Text--right o-Size--1of5">Type</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <th class="c-Text--left"><code>.o-Container</code></th>
        <td>Sets max-width of element to the global max width</td>
